content.description: Sit start at sharp left facing corner.  Fire up to good hold and easy topout.  Too bad it's not bigger because the feature is cool.
content.protection: Pad, landing has been smoothed over by mountain bikers.
content.location: Just left of the main upper wall.

content.description: Don't know if this has ever been done but seems like there should be a problem in the middle of the face.  Not sure if it can be started from a sit.
Don't know if this has ever been done but it seems like there is a problem on the right side of the wall. Sit start at good ledge and then either go straight up or traverse left.
Sit start at roof around the right, fire up and move left along good holds to the same topout as for Johnny D.
content.protection: Pad and spotter, landing area is small.
content.location: Around the right at small roof.

content.description: Start standing on right side of face and move up and slightly left to topout.
content.protection: Pad, landing has been improved by mountain bikers.

content.description: A sit start problem working up the far right side of the main face.
content.location: Sit start on the right corner same as Johnny D Arete. Work left into the main face making a large move into the final crimp of Artemis Providence and topping out the same.

content.description: A fun technical problem traversing left to right through sharp crimps. If you want to spice it up a little instead of traversing all the way into the arete dyno to the top from the large crimp rail. Would call it a classic if it weren't for the chossy feet.
content.location: Sit start on the solid incut hold to the left of the main face. Traverse your way right into a double gaston crux, finishing up the right arete. Traverses its way through the two projects listed. Probably goes at closer to a V6 but since this is my anti-style it felt more like a V7.

content.description: Cool overhanging wall up at the top of the Super Crack 2 boulder.  Landing has been improved by the mountain biking crew.
